<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 17 at 9:16PM CST  by NWS Norman-Oklahoma City</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northern Jefferson
and southern Stephens Counties through 945 PM CST...
At 916 PM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Addington, moving east at 45 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Waurika, Comanche, Velma, Loco, Addington and Waurika Lake.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
